President Muhammadu Buhari has sent condolences to the immediate family of former Lagos State Commissioner of Police, Abubakar Tsav, over his passage. The President also commiserated with the government and people of Benue State over Tsav’s death, noting that his wise counsels to leaders at both state and national levels would be missed very much. In a statement issued by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu, President Buhari said “I feel very special about people like Tsav, who took great personal risks to defend me and my government in all situations and circumstances”. According to the statement, President Buhari “condoles with government and people of Benue State over the passing of an illustrious son, Abubakar Tsav, who was a former Lagos State Commissioner of Police. “The President joins family members, friends and associates in mourning the retired police officer, whose years in service continue to resonate with the discipline and focus he brought into security operations, particularly in Lagos State. “President Buhari notes, with sadness, that the vociferous voice of Tsav, will be sorely missed, while acknowledging that his wise counsels to leaders in his state, and national level, especially on good governance were most timely and impactful. “The President prays for the repose of his soul, urging the family to find strength in his contributions to humanity”, the statement said.